 one of the earliest economic papers on FDA approval speed and it establishes a key stylized fact: \textbf{Approval speed is endogenous to drug importance.}
\par
So in investigating whether faster FDA approval {$\rightarrow$} diversion risk?

it becomes hella important to consider the potential endogeniety / selection bias in any approval-speed analysis b/c this paper shows that Drug importance {$\rightarrow$} faster approval},
  file = {/Users/alexdelatorre/Zotero/storage/KEUQ72FU/Dranove and Meltzer - 1994 - Do Important Drugs Reach the Market Sooner.pdf}
}

